processinfo.head: Processing Information

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents

did.unittitle: [Report of a petition of the gentry and clergy against the Canons of 1640, and the Etcetera Oath, 1640]

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p:
3 p.
Contemporary MS.

objections to the canons and the
oath, and the text of the petition
addressed to the Privy Council. Henry
Bourchier, earl of Bath (1587-1654),
is reported to have been the first
signer, and the county's M.P.'s to
have delivered it. Thomas Wise
(c.1605-1641); Edward Seymour
(1610-1688).
f.9.

did.unittitle: GREAT BRITAIN. PARLIAMENT, 1644. HOUSE OF COMMONS.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p:
[1644 June]
1 p.
Contemporary MS copy in the hand of
Algernon Percy, 10th earl of
Northumberland. Concerns Lord
Conway's betrayal of Lord Chandos'
intention of leaving the King at
Oxford. This is the examination of
Chandos by a Parliamentary committee.
See The Parliamentary or
Constitutional History of England, by
Several Hands, 2nd ed, 13, p.210-214.
George Brydges, baron Chandos of
Sudeley (1620-1655); Edward Conway,
baron Conway of Ragley (1594-1655);
Edward Sackville, earl of Dorset
(1590-1652).
f.12.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p:
1 p.

and his son. Concerning letters in
the custody of members of the
Committee of Both Kingdoms which were
taken by Jean de Montreuil. Algernon
Percy, 10th earl of Northumberland
(1602-1668); Sir Philip Stapleton
(1603-1647).
f.13.
